&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Medical Secretary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ONCOLOGY/HAEMATOLOGY DIRECTORATE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1 x Full-time Post (37.5 hours per week)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 4&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Oncology &amp; Haematology Department is seeking to appoint a Medical Secretary to join their busy department.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Your main responsibilities will be to provide a comprehensive, confidential and quality medical secretarial service to consultants and junior doctors.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate must have the ability to deal with highly confidential information and use their discretion when necessary. They will have the ability to prioritise and manage their workload independently and experience in audio/ touch typing is essential, as well as the ability to demonstrate a sound knowledge of medical terminology.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name :Amie Gillespie, Job title: Administration Manager, Telephone number: 01604 523738 Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Amie Gillespie, Admin manager on 01604 543738&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
